                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is working at an immigration clinic that provides health checks and health education for immigrants and refugees. What need(s) are essential for the nurse to focus on when caring for this population of clients? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nImmigrant and refugee clients need health care regardless of insurance status. Acculturation puts this population at risk because they begin to pick up American culture practices that may be unhealthy in an attempt to fit in. Vaccinations need to be offered to provide protection and build immunity to a new environment. Educating clients about what migration means to them does not offer any health benefits to the client. Immigrant clients do not always experience health conditions through the migration process. Finally, clients with known communicable health conditions would be treated prior to entering a new country of residence.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, essential, and the subject, health considerations for immigrants and refugees. It is necessary to understand what their primary needs are for health promotion, acculturation, overcoming cultural barriers, and safety to assist to answer this question.",
                        "id": "163518e32a4b4defb8f1bd92cf8e9c5f",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
